		\section{Conclusion}
		
		This paper presented OASIS, a topology-aware orchestration framework for SLA-constrained SFC placement in heterogeneous Multi-RAT environments. By integrating graph-based representations with learning-driven decision making and QoS-aware path realization via SR, OASIS enables efficient and scalable orchestration under complex infrastructure constraints. The framework leverages telemetry-driven topology awareness and operator objectives for adaptive SFC orchestration. Overall, OASIS demonstrates the effectiveness of combining topology-aware learning with cloud-native orchestration and SR-based transport mechanisms for next-generation Multi-RAT networks.
		
